'''Eurosolar''' is the non-profit European Association for Renewable Energy ({{lang-de|Europäische Vereinigung für Erneuerbare Energien}}) that conducts its work independently of [[Political party|political parties]], [[institution]]s, [[commercial enterprise]]s, and [[interest group]]s. Eurosolar develops and encourages political and economic [[action plan]]s and concepts for the introduction of [[renewable energy]]. The association has offices in 14 countries that include Austria, Italy, Turkey, and Ukraine. Eurosolar has approximately 2,500 members, close to 400 legal groups, {{citation needed|date=March 2015}} and owns the ''Solar Age'' magazine, released on a quarterly basis.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eurosolar.de/de/images/stories/pdf/media-daten-2010.pdf |title=Solar Age Media Information |date=30 July 2010 |work=Solar Age |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref> A history of the association is available.<ref name="samuel-2013"> {{cite book | first = Gert | last = Samuel | translator-first1 = Silvia | translator-last1 = Strauch | translator-first2 = Martina R | translator-last2 = Jones | title = 25 years of EUROSOLAR: 1988–2013 | date = August 2013 | publisher = EUROSOLAR, Europäische Vereinigung für Erneuerbare Energien | location = Bonn, Germany | url = http://www.eurosolar.de/en/images/stories/publikationen/Eurosolar25_engl.pdf | access-date = 2016-08-05 }}</ref>
Formed on 2 August 1988 in [[Bonn]], [[West Germany]],<ref name="samuel-2013"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eurosolar.de/en/index.php/events-2013-archivmenuevents-169/595-anniversary-celebrations-25-years-of-eurosolar |title=Eurosolar's anniversary |date=24 August 2013 |work=Eurosolar |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref> Eurosolar runs an annual event called the Solar Prize awards, rewarding progress in renewable energy.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eurosolar.de/en/index.php/solar-prizes-mainmenu-24/european-solar-prizes-2014 |title=Solar Prize Archives |date=24 November 2014 |work=Eurosolar |accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref>
