{{Infobox power station | name = Henderson Station One | image = | image_caption = | location_map = USA Kentucky | country = United States | location = [[Henderson, Kentucky|Henderson]], [[Kentucky]] | coordinates = {{coord|37.84|N|87.59|W|region:US-KY_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | owner = City of Henderson | status = | th_fuel_primary = [[Bituminous coal]] | th_cooling_source = [[Ohio River]] | th_combined_cycle = | ps_units_operational = 3 | ps_electrical_capacity = 44 [[Megawatt|MW]] | commissioned = 1956 | decommissioned = 2008 }}
'''Henderson Station One (HMP&L One)''' was a [[Fossil fuel power station|coal-fired power station]] owned and operated by the city of [[Henderson, Kentucky]].
Citing rising costs and mounting environmental regulations, Henderson Municipal Power and Light closed its 58-year-old Station One power plant on Water Street by December 31, 2008.<ref name="Stinnet">Chuck Stinnet, [http://www.courierpress.com/news/2008/aug/27/henderson-power-plant-close/ "Henderson power plant to close"] Courier Press, August 27, 2008</ref>
It has since been replaced by Henderson Station Two (HMP&L Two) as a part of [[Sebree Station]].
