The '''slash rating''', under the United States [[National Electrical Code]], is given to circuit interrupt hardware and specifies a maximum line-to-ground voltage rating in combination with a maximum line-to-line voltage rating.  One common application would be for a [[three-phase]] [[electrical load]]s.  For example a 120/240 V rating can disqualify a circuit breaker for use with a delta system load that would otherwise work with a wye system load.

