'''Trimdon Grange Wind Farm''' is an [[Wind farm#Onshore|onshore wind farm]] near [[Trimdon Grange]], [[County Durham]], [[England]]. Commissioned in October 2008 it consists of four 1.3&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]] [[Nordex]] N60 [[Wind turbine|turbines]] giving a total capacity of 5.2&nbsp;MW. It was developed by [[Électricité de France|EDF]] and is operated by [[Cumbria Wind Farms]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-12-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102132011/http://www.bwea.com/ukwed/operational.asp |archivedate=2012-11-02 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.thewindpower.net/wind-farm-1531-trimdon-grange-nordex-n60-1300.php</ref>
The proposed location of the wind farm caused controversy in 2004 when an agent of [[Tony Blair]], then [[Prime Minister]], wrote to a local action group, Trimdon Area Group Against Wind Farms, claiming that the site was unsuitable. The location is about one mile from Tony Blair's old constituency house.<ref>https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/pandora/wind-farms-not-on-the-prime-ministers-doorstep-thanks-689504.html</ref>
